Parents and guests invited for the 10th biennial inter-house sports competition of Great Heights Academy, Kado Estate, Abuja, were astonished by the athletic display of the students. City & Crime reports that four houses, red, blue, yellow and green, took part in the sporting activities which included relays, egg race, marchpast and hand ball. A member of the Local Organising Committee (LOC) of the event, Isiaka Raheem, told our City Editor that at the end of the event which held at the Aguiyi Ironsi Cantonment, red house emerged the overall best, followed by blue house. Earlier, the proprietor of the school, Hajiya Rabi Namtari, said the school was investing in sporting activities to build both the physical and mental abilities of the students, while thanking parents for their support to the school. The principal of the school, Hajiya Hussaina Abdul, commended the students and the staff of the academy for their dedication and support for the event. Highlights of the event included the presentation of awards to the participating houses and a football match between the staff of the secondary and primary sections of the school.